---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Hong Kong Tax Deadline Calendar 2025: Filing Dates and Provisional Tax";
const description = "Hong Kong tax deadline calendar for 2025. Learn key tax filing dates, provisional tax deadlines, and how to avoid penalties with our Hong Kong tax calculator.";
const image = "/images/blogs/hong-kong-tax-deadline-calendar.svg";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} image={image}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-canvas dark:bg-primary">
    <main class="min-h-screen">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6 text-sm">
          <ol class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><a href="/" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Home</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><a href="/blogs" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Blogs</a></li>
            <li class="flex items-center gap-2"><span class="text-muted">/</span><span class="font-medium text-ink dark:text-on-primary" aria-current="page">Hong Kong Tax Deadline Calendar</span></li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <article class="prose max-w-none">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-4 dark:text-on-primary">Hong Kong Tax Deadline Calendar 2025: Filing Dates and Provisional Tax</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-body dark:text-muted">Last updated: July 2026 | 10 min read</p>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-body dark:text-muted">
            <p>Missing a Hong Kong tax deadline can result in surcharges, penalties, and even legal action. The Inland Revenue Department operates on a strict calendar for issuing tax returns, receiving filings, and collecting payments. This guide covers the key tax filing dates for 2025, including when tax returns are issued, filing deadlines for individuals and businesses, provisional tax deadlines, how to request an extension, and penalties for late payment. Use our <a href="/countries/hong-kong/salaries-tax/salaries-tax-calculator" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax calculator</a> to estimate your liability before the deadline.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Key Tax Filing Dates for 2025</h2>
            <p>The IRD issues individual tax returns each year covering the preceding year of assessment. For the 2024/25 year of assessment, tax returns are typically issued starting in May 2025. The exact issue date varies based on your profile, but you generally have one month from the issue date to file your return. If you need more time, you can apply for a short extension, though the IRD does not grant automatic universal extensions. Keep an eye on your mailbox and the IRD website for the exact issue date.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Salaries Tax Return Deadlines</h2>
            <p>Salaries tax returns are issued to individuals who obtain income from employment or office. The standard filing deadline is one month from the date of the return. For example, if your BIR60 is issued on June 2, 2025, the due date is July 2, 2025. Late filing attracts a penalty of up to HK$10,000. If you are organized and file early, you can avoid the stress of last-minute submissions and reduce the risk of penalties. Self-assessment is available for straightforward cases.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Profits Tax Return Deadlines</h2>
            <p>Profits tax returns for businesses are issued based on the company's year-end date. The IRD sets issue dates ranging from early April to late August for different year-end profiles. For example:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
              <li>December year-end: Return issued by April 2, file within one month</li>
              <li>March year-end: Return issued by the second Monday of May or later</li>
              <li>Small businesses may receive later issue dates to facilitate compliance</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Always check the exact due date on the return itself. For a complete schedule, see our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-tax-deadline-calendar" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax deadline calendar</a> overview.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Provisional Tax Deadlines</h2>
            <p>Provisional tax for both salaries tax and profits tax is typically payable in two installments. The first installment is due in November of the current year, and the second installment is due in April of the following year. The exact dates are shown on the provisional tax demand note. Missing these deadlines results in a 5% surcharge, with an additional 10% surcharge if the tax remains unpaid after six months. Keeping a calendar reminder for these dates helps you manage your cash flow. See our <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-provisional-tax-guide" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong provisional tax guide</a> for strategies to manage provisional payments.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Extension Requests</h2>
            <p>If you are unable to file by the deadline, you may request a short extension. For individual returns, the IRD considers applications for extension on a case-by-case basis. You can submit an extension request electronically through eTAX or in writing. Provide reasons for the delay, such as missing documents or exceptional circumstances. For business returns, the IRD may automatically allow a longer period if it is justified. However, extensions do not eliminate the surcharge for late payment of provisional tax.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Penalties for Missing Deadlines</h2>
            <p>Failure to file a tax return on time exposes you to a maximum penalty of HK$10,000. Withholding information or providing false information in a tax return may result in prosecution. Late payment of provisional tax or final tax attracts an initial 5% surcharge on the unpaid amount. After six months, an additional 10% surcharge is imposed. The IRD may also take recovery action, including issuing a warrant to collect the tax. To avoid these consequences, file and pay on time, and use our <a href="/countries/hong-kong/salaries-tax/salaries-tax-calculator" class="text-link hover:underline dark:text-link">Hong Kong tax calculator</a> to estimate your liability early.</p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">When are Hong Kong tax returns issued?</h3>
            <p>Individual tax returns are typically issued from early May each year. Business tax returns are issued based on the company's year-end date, generally from early April to late August.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">What is the penalty for late filing?</h3>
            <p>The IRD may impose a penalty of up to HK$10,000 for failing to file a tax return on time. Serious cases may result in prosecution.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Can I pay provisional tax in installments?</h3>
            <p>Provisional tax is automatically structured in two installments. If you cannot pay, contact the IRD immediately to discuss installment arrangements rather than ignoring the demand note.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">How do I avoid fines for missing deadlines?</h3>
            <p>File your return within the specified one-month period and pay any tax due on time. Use eTAX to manage your payments and set reminders. Where possible, pay provisional tax early to reduce surcharge risk.</p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink dark:text-on-primary">Is there a universal extension period for Hong Kong tax?</h3>
            <p>No. The IRD does not grant automatic extensions. You must apply for an extension on a case-by-case basis through eTAX or in writing, and approval is not guaranteed.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink mb-6 dark:text-on-primary">Related Calculators</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
              <a href="/countries/hong-kong/salaries-tax/salaries-tax-calculator" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">HK Salaries Tax Calculator</a>
              <a href="/countries/hong-kong/profits-tax/profits-tax-calculator" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">HK Profits Tax Calculator</a>
              <a href="/countries/hong-kong" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">More Hong Kong Calculators</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-12">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink mb-6 dark:text-on-primary">Related Articles</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
              <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-etax-guide" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">Hong Kong eTAX Guide</a>
              <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-provisional-tax-guide" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">Hong Kong Provisional Tax Guide</a>
              <a href="/blogs/hong-kong-salaries-tax-guide" class="block rounded border p-4 hover:border-primary transition">Hong Kong Salaries Tax Guide</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
